Fewer patrons to serve and an earlier curfew. That's the reality for many in the restaurant industry. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu takes a look at how the news of tighter COVID-19 restrictions has been received. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Half a loaf is better than no bread at all. That's how some staff at a restaurant in Tembisa in Kempton Park feel after tighter COVID-19 restrictions have been imposed. Establishments have to close at 9pm ahead of the curfew now starting at 10pm. READ: SA Lockdown: South Africa moves to alert level 3 Only 50 people are allowed indoors and 100 people outdoors. While the latest restrictions mean less business, those in charge are grateful their doors can remain open at all. * eNCA’s Lindokuhle Xulu reports.